```
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_API_URL         # Backend API base URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL             # Frontend app URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_CDN_URL             # CDN URL for assets
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENVIRONMENT         # "local" | "dev" | "prod"
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
NEXTAUTH_SECRET
NEXTAUTH_URL
```

## Code Style Rules

- **Constants**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (exported and module-level)
- **Enums**: PascalCase name, PascalCase members (e.g., `UserRole.Seller`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase, defined in `model/types.ts`
- **Components**: One component per file, named export (except Next.js pages which re-export as default)
- **Hooks/utilities**: kebab-case filenames
- **Props destructured** on first line of component body
- **Always use braces** for `if` blocks (except single-line early returns)
- **No barrel files** in most places — only `index.ts` in `widgets`, `entities`, `features`, `shared/ui`, `shared/lib`
- **Variable names**: minimum 2 characters (`error` not `e`, `event` not `e`)

## Linting

Biome is used (via `ultracite`) instead of ESLint for linting. Config is in `biome.jsonc`.

Pre-commit hook runs: `lint:types && lint && test`.

## Testing

Jest with `ts-jest` and `@testing-library/react`. Tests are co-located with the code they test (`.test.ts` next to the source file). Examples in `src/shared/lib/`.

The `@/*` path alias maps to `src/` (configured in `tsconfig.json` and `jest.config.ts`).
